  "texts": [
    "The four bins for airspace opacity are presented as 15.590 (95% CI: 14.809 to 16.401), 17.940 (95% CI: 17.198 to 18.718), 22.414 (95% CI: 20.828 to 24.185) and 41.076 (95% CI: 33.894 to 48.061).",
    "The five bins for atelectasis are presented as 11.550 (95% CI: 10.558 to 12.505), 10.638 (95% CI: 10.030 to 11.221), 11.366 (95% CI: 10.070 to 12.691), 9.777 (95% CI: 7.909 to 11.676) and 12.262 (95% CI: 9.144 to 15.681).",
    "The five bins for bacterial/lobar pneumonia are presented as 4.191 (95% CI: 3.645 to 4.745), 4.443 (95% CI: 4.069 to 4.842), 5.474 (95% CI: 4.499 to 6.499), 6.619 (95% CI: 4.202 to 9.317) and 9.861 (95% CI: 7.620 to 12.169).",
    "The five bins for cardiomediastinal abnormality are presented as 14.061 (95% CI: 13.295 to 14.817), 16.268 (95% CI: 15.609 to 16.867), 21.241 (95% CI: 19.556 to 22.881), 24.820 (95% CI: 20.349 to 29.464) and 34.358 (95% CI: 30.263 to 38.553).",
    "The five bins for cardiomegaly are presented as 10.169 (95% CI: 9.615 to 10.727), 14.611 (95% CI: 13.737 to 15.516), 19.483 (95% CI: 16.558 to 22.551), 39.736 (95% CI: 32.091 to 46.737) and 26.732 (95% CI: 17.879 to 35.100)."
  ],
